Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the development of a more efficient network architecture. The paper also discusses energy consumption and memory usage, which could place it under the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and resource-constrained environments could make it relevant to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
